HEADWORD: Nitrocalcite
<hw>Ni`tro*cal"cite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Nitro-</ets> + <ets>calcite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>Nitrate of calcium, a substance having a grayish white color,
occurring in efflorescences on old walls, and in limestone caves,
especially where there exists decaying animal matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

